code not run only shown for documentation

f <- '/Users/schmidm/Documents/other_people_to_and_from/ClaudiaI/MS_PASHA/unscaled_deeptools_out/RefSeqGRCh37.3_deeptools_summary.count'

unscaled <- arsRtools::load_chip_matrix(f, chip_samples_table) %>%
  mutate(mean_value = value/(end-start))

body_scaled <- unscaled %>%
  mutate(id=paste0(id,':',end-start)) %>%
  arsRtools::scale_chip_matrix(., scales = Refseq_pc_g2k_q1_second_half_body_scales) %>%
  separate(id, c('gene_id', 'gene_name', 'length'), sep=':', convert = T)

Same but instead of sum of signal inside genes, divide by length to get mean per length

(body_scale_mat_means <- body_scaled %>%
    mutate(siRNA = ifelse(siRNA == 'siFFL', 'siFFL', 'KD'),
           scaled_BGSub_ChIP = scaled_BGSub_ChIP/length) %>%
    dplyr::select(siRNA, main_run, run, scaled_BGSub_ChIP, gene_id, gene_name) %>%
    filter(scaled_BGSub_ChIP > 0) %>%
    tidyr::spread(siRNA, scaled_BGSub_ChIP))

  geom_point(size=.1, color='gray') +
  geom_abline(slope=1, color='orange') +

get DESeq2 results

load('../data/RNAseq/Refseqv3_introns_DESeq2_results.RData', verbose=T)
## Loading objects:
##   Refseq_introns_DESeq2_results

and add intron class annotation

(introns_df <- Refseq_introns_DESeq2_results %>% 
  mutate(intron_class = case_when( 
              .$padj < .1 & .$log2FoldChange < 0 ~ 'intron_down',
              .$padj < .1 & .$log2FoldChange > 0 ~ 'intron_up')) %>%
  dplyr::select(id, main_run, intron_class) %>%
  tbl_df %>%
  separate(id, c('gene_id', 'gene_name'), sep=':'))

d_means <- left_join(body_scale_mat_means, introns_df) %>%
  mutate(log_ratio = log2(KD/siFFL))

violin plots

violins_means <- d_means %>%
  filter(!is.na(intron_class), 
         !is.na(log_ratio)) %>%
ggplot(., aes(x=intron_class, y=log_ratio, fill=intron_class)) +
  geom_violin() +
  facet_grid(.~main_run) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype=1, color='orange') +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = 'Set1') +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + 
  geom_boxplot(width=.2, fill='gray', outlier.size = NA) +
  ggtitle('body scaled BGsub mean inside gene')

violins_means

wilcox p-values for the difference

Wilcox intron_up != intron_down:

d_means %>%
  filter(!is.na(intron_class), 
         !is.na(log_ratio)) %>%
  dplyr::select(main_run, run, gene_id, intron_class, log_ratio) %>%
  spread(intron_class, log_ratio) %>%
  group_by(main_run) %>%
  do(tidy(wilcox.test(.$intron_up, .$intron_down))) %>%
  kable
main_run statistic p.value method alternative
CI siARS2 4663107 0.0000000 Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction two.sided
MA siZ18 1830894 0.0000000 Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction two.sided
MA siRRP40 5014385 0.9875634 Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction two.sided

Welch wilcox for KD <|> CTRL:
here we compare the genes side-by-side so a pairwise test seems appropriated (also more fitting the representation of log-fold changes in the violon plots )

d_means %>%
  filter(!is.na(intron_class), 
         !is.na(log_ratio)) %>%
group_by(main_run, intron_class) %>%
  do(tidy(wilcox.test(.$KD, .$siFFL, alternative = 'greater', paired=TRUE))) %>%
  kable
